          "correctOptionId": "opt-1",
          "explanation": "- Atropine is obtained from atropa belladonna. - It is non selective muscarinic receptor antagonist Physostigmine is the specific antidote for poisoning with belladonna . It crosses blood-brain barrier and antagonises both central and peripheral actions. Physostigmine sometimes itself induces hypotension, arrhythmias and undesirable central effects. It is therefore employed only as a last reso. Neostigmine does not block the central effect, but is less risky.",
