          "correctOptionId": "opt-1",
          "explanation": "Thiazides cause hyperlipidemia as adverse effect and thus cannot be used to treat this condition. Indications of thiazides: Diuretic Uses: Non-diuretic Uses: Hypeension (First line drugs) Congestive hea failure Diabetes insipidus Idiopathic hypercalciurea with Nephrocalcinosis Loop diuretics cause hypocalcemia by increasing the excretion of Ca2+ whereas thiazides cause hypercalcemia by decreasing its excretion. Thiazides reduce the excretion of Ca++ in the kidney, so can be used for the treatment of patients with hypercalciuria and recurrent Ca++ stones in the kidney.",
