          "correctOptionId": "opt-1",
          "explanation": "Anti histamines are classified into first generation and second generation compounds on the basis of CNS penetration and anti cholinergic propeies. First generation anti-histamine can penetrate blood brain barrier and possess additional anti cholinergic propeies which are lacking in second generation drugs. Cyclizine is a first generation where as cetrizine, loratidine and fexofenadine are second generation drugs Refer Goodman & Gilman 12/e p921",
